{"amendments":[{"body":"Make the new trace-capture test deterministic in `tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs:572-596`. It currently uses `#[tokio::test(flavor = \"multi_thread\")]` together with `tracing::subscriber::set_default(...)`, but `set_default` only installs the subscriber for the current thread. Since `service.invoke(request).await` contains await points, the future can resume on a different Tokio worker and emit `\"invocation completed\"` outside the test subscriber, causing intermittent failures. Use `flavor = \"current_thread\"` for this test or switch to a capture mechanism that applies across worker threads.","rationale":"This is a real CI stability risk introduced by the new test: the assertion depends on thread-local tracing state in a multithreaded async test, so it can fail nondeterministically as scheduling changes."}],"summary":"Reviewed the diff against `origin/master`, read the touched implementation files end-to-end, and ran `cargo test` plus `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`; both passed. The backend token/cache handling changes look correct overall. The one issue I found is a new tracing test that is vulnerable to nondeterministic failure on Tokio's multithread runtime."}